The BBC understands that the DE's aim is to have a common test in place by November 2017. The DE have suggested that they might consult on three options:
a) Continue with current systems of teacher assessment at the end of KS2;
b) Use a model for assessment based on that of the Scottish National Standardised Assessment;
c) Have external tests for all pupils in all subjects every year in the summer term.
